Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the creation of disjunctive concept definitions, which is a common approach in rule learning. The paper also discusses the problem of small disjuncts, which is a well-known issue in rule learning. 

Probabilistic Methods are present in the text as the paper investigates the impact of noise on learning. Probabilistic methods are commonly used to model uncertainty and noise in data, and the paper discusses how noise affects learning in two different domains.
